[1] Data Sources (On‑prem / ADF upserts)
        │
        ▼
[2] Azure Cosmos DB (Transactional containers)
        │   (any insert/update)
        ▼
[3] Change Feed  ──► [3a] Lease Container (checkpoints)
        │
        ▼
[4] Azure Function (Cosmos DB trigger; one method per container)
        │
        ├─(A) Load Config for this container
        │       - Blob: /config/<container>/events.json  (rules)
        │       - Blob: /config/<container>/tracked.json (field list)
        │
        ├─(B) Read current Baseline Snapshot from Blob (if any)
        │       - Blob: /data/<container>/<docId>.json   (versioned)
        │
        ├─(C) Decide CREATE vs MODIFY
        │       - No baseline → CREATE
        │       - Has baseline → MODIFY
        │
        ├─(D) Compute Changes (delta) for tracked fields
        │       - From baseline vs newDoc
        │
        ├─(E) Evaluate Events (rules) against:
        │       - CREATE: only events with "when: insert" (use eq/exists checks)
        │       - MODIFY: events with "when: update" (use changed/becameNotNull/eq)
        │
        ├─(F) For each matched event → Build message payload
        │       - include: container, docId, eventId, changed fields, newDoc slices
        │
        ├─(G) Send to Service Bus (Queue/Topic)
        │
        ├─(H) Post‑Send snapshot management in Blob
        │       - CREATE: create baseline (idempotent; If‑None‑Match)
        │       - MODIFY: overwrite id.json (blob versioning keeps history)
        │
        └─(I) Error path (never throw away)
                - Write error record to /errors/<container>/<date>/<docId>-*.json
                - Include reason, docId, function invocation id, raw input (truncated)

                (Function completes)